reviews.text: St. John’sChurch is one of the oldest medieval architectural monuments in Latvia. Church was built in the beginning of 13th century during the Christianization of Baltic’s for the purposes of the Livonian Holy Order because residence of the order was located in Cēsis; therefore Cēsis became one of the most important German power centers in the Baltic’s from 1237 up to 1561

Pretty, very old, church with a terrifying (fun) option to tour the bell tower. The church is pretty, but let's be honest - all churches from that era are. For mere 2€ you can take your life in your hands and climb the stairs of the ~65m bell tower for a view. Most of the thrill comes from navigating the near-black steep staircase on your way up. Still, I enjoyed it.
A good place

The church facade still awaits restoration, but the community seems to be very active. The guide, a senior lady, is very vigorous, helpful and gave lots of information, as did the exhibitions inside. The tombs of the Masters of the Livonian Order and the stained glass with the Latvian coat of arms, which was miraculosly preserved by the pastor during the Soviet time are impressive.
Nice church, nothing special.
Very good food and service
The best affordable place in Las Mercedes
Excelent place to eat Italian food
The best pizza in Mercedes neighborhood.
good for pizzas

Always enjoy eating here. One of Fredericton's local favorites.

Awesome warm and friendly atmosphere, fun staff, good local beer selection, and  really great pub fare / comfort food menu.

Overall, a great place to go out for a casual and relaxed dinner or evening meal. Oh, and a great deal on Wednesdays when apps are half price (remember to buy a drink)!

Everything about Snooty warms my heart. The staff are always amazing and friendly. Lots of good beer. They have an upper deck patio in the warmer months and a side room that comfortably fits up to 20 of your homies (I requested said room for my birthday and crammed 20+ in there and it was awesome!) Do yourself a favour and order some Duke Rolls while you're visiting!

A popular pub located in the heart of downtown Fredericton, the Snooty Fox has a reputation for being a great social hangout. If the weather is good you can sit on the roof level of the establishment which is the best choice in the summer. If visiting from out of New Brunswick I recommend trying some of the local brews they offer. Picaroons is always a good choice.
My third  time coming here, and always a good experience. Good food,  good service, and great local beer taps. Always a fun and friendly crowd. A must visit if in Fredericton!
We were a group of 25, and got served fairly quickly. Friendly staff. Good choices on tap.

A must stop for the best French Onion Soup I've ever had!  The pork buttons & beef wellingtons appetizers were also right up at the top! The Classic Ceasar was the best we had in town complete with a pickled green bean! Our waiter was amazing, informative & helpful not only about the restaurant but the town as well. This is the oldest restaurant in Banff & well worth a visit!

Just had our fourth meal here during our 2 week stay.  Excellent place. So relaxing and the staff are brilliant. I only suggest that you increase the pool tables by another 1 or 2. Plenty of room. When we visit in the summer we will come back through. Thanks for our meals .
From what I remember a really fun bar! The cod was delicious

Where to start this little dive has to be my favorite place delicious food great staff good music! 
Overall a great time!
Especially on $4 beer night ;)
Got to see my favourite bands here! Not the best if you are short and it’s a full house, but people are always nice, drinks and staff are great!

Minus one star for being open-air (self opinion). Myself just prefers air-conditioned. Except that, this is the best food mall I ever know. It is ranged from fair class food to medium-high. So that is suit for every age range.

Dude I love this Shopping Mall this is really great and has a lot of things to see. At the source surrounded by several other Shopping Malls where you can find everything. It is definitely worth it if you spent time in bkk

Locating next to Siam BTS. The place is full of eateries. They have Chinese, Korean, Japanese, Thai etc kind of food serving restaurants. If you want to eat something it is the correct place for you. Besides the mall also has section for fashion on the lower level. Behind the mall is another walking area where you might find an interesting place to eat and stores you might want to take a look into. It's a good place to explore at night.

Good enough place, i would however recommend that a center with such a huge turn over could afford more bins, and possibly a more interesting variety than the same old stuff found at every other shopping center. Other than that, it looks good, has some interesting things for sale.

On the other side of Siam Paragon in Bangkok, Siam Square One is another shopping mall. It serves many local restaurants as well as international cuisine. The Line Village shop is also located in this mall.
